I recently underwent a dental implant procedure at Life Time Dental in Marathalli, Bengaluru, and I am delighted to share my outstanding experience with Dr. Sharon. My journey with Dr. Sharon began 15 years ago when I sought her expertise for a root canal and crown procedure. Remarkably, the crown she provided lasted a phenomenal 15 years, far surpassing the expected lifespan of 7 years. This alone speaks volumes about Dr. Sharon's proficiency and commitment to her patients' long-term oral health.

Returning to Dr. Sharon for the implant procedure, I was once again impressed by her exceptional skill and efficiency. From the moment I walked into her office, I felt reassured by her warm demeanor and confident approach. Dr. Sharon meticulously explained every aspect of the implant process, ensuring that I felt fully informed and comfortable throughout.

What truly sets Dr. Sharon apart is her unparalleled speed and efficiency in performing the implant procedure. In my opinion, she is unmatched in her field, delivering results with remarkable precision and swiftness. The implant she provided not only looks incredibly natural but also functions flawlessly, enhancing both my smile and confidence.

I must also commend the entire team at Life Time Dental for their professionalism and dedication to patient care. From the receptionists to the dental assistants, everyone contributed to making my experience seamless and enjoyable.

In conclusion, I wholeheartedly recommend Dr. Sharon and Life Time Dental to anyone seeking top-notch dental care in Bengaluru. Dr. Sharon's exceptional skill, coupled with her dedication to patient satisfaction, makes her the go-to dentist for anyone in need of dental implants or other procedures. Thank you, Dr. Sharon, for your outstanding service and for restoring my smile with the fastest and most efficient implant in the country!
Doctor Sharon explains so well.Her treatment is perfect.very patiently treats.She is so particular about Perfection.will surely recommend to others too.
Well furnished and hygienic. Doctor’s behaviour is good and explanations are very helpful . The clinic is not for the lower middle class people like me.

I had recently visited Lifetime Dental to cure my ailing tooth during the lockdown. Obviously, I was very apprehensive of visiting the clinic given the current situation and tried to defer the visit for long. I had cancelled my appointment once before finally making up my mind to see the doctor. I stepped into the clinic with lot of notions and concerns about being safe however within few minutes of my visit to clinic, all of those concerns were swept off. Upon my entry, they asked me to wear a shoe cover and sanitize my hands. They took temperature reading and a pulse oximeter reading and then asked me to remove my mask and place it in a paper bag to avoid any contamination. After all this, I could see the doctor. The doctor listened to my problem with patience and intent, took some X-rays and started the treatment. The doctor who treated me was wearing masks, face-shield, and a PPE kit as a precautionary measure to ensure safety vice-versa.  The doctors were very professional and my whole experience of visiting the clinic was just wonderful.

Fantastic experience with Dr Sharon! She explained everything beforehand very well. The wisdom tooth extraction went smoothly in her hands. Utmost care was taken. Very professional. 
And Dr Gayatri on her team has to be mentioned for a thorough job done
I have been a regular at Lifetime Dental for over a decade
Many thanks Dr Sharon

Dr.Sharon and her team at Lifetime Dental Clinic are true professionals who have helped with all my dental needs. The clinic uses state-of-the-art technology during my procedures and the support staff kept me informed of all the steps and were incredibly knowledgeable. I had even been to the clinic in the midst of COVID during which the hygiene level was top-notch. I also appreciate the fact that I can call Dr.Sharon for any dental questions and she addresses them immediately and patiently. Overall, I go to the clinic every 6 months for a check-up and would highly recommend this clinic based on my extremely positive experience!

When I had first visited her 3 years back for an impacted wisdom tooth extraction and dental crown, I was very much satisfied with the treatment. That's why I decided to visit her again for removal of another impacted wisdom tooth. Since I had travelled from a place 2600 kilometres from her clinic and I just had a day to stay in Bangalore, I decided to get RCT, bleaching and scaling too along with extraction. She is very helpful and she made sure that everything was done on time with no delay at all. All the procedures were done seamlessly. My brother who is very much scared of RCTs got 3 RCTs done at her clinic and he didn't even realise how smoothly it was done. Next time if he ever has to visit a dentist, he said he is going to her clinic straight away and I totally agree with him !

My family has been going to Dr Sharon Colaco Dias since 2007.
We go to her because she  is very experienced and is highly qualified,
** ****** **  ************ ***  takes time to explain the dental issue and the treatment. The dental procedures have been painless and smooth in general,complete with follow up advise and check ups.
As her patients , I appreciate the personal attention and time given to my family and me by Dr Sharon .
I also feel good about  the high standard of hygiene that is maintained in her state of the art clinic.

I went to her for toothache. I was asked to do 3 root canals and the total bill amout would be around 80 to 90 thousand including drilling/cleaning/filling/capping etc (Costliest caps will take it to 1.2 Lacs). She gave me other options like extraction/bridge etc.but all of them were over costly and needed the operation. She wanted me to undergo the treatment right away with no concern; or to look at the possibility of any alternative treatment which is not this harsh. I came home did gargal with warm slat water which was recommended by some other doctor earlier and it worked just fine. Its been over 4 months and i never had the toothache again. So, I would say it's little costly here.
